{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/moving-from-medium-to-static-blog/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Tiago Brito","author":"Tiago Brito"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"b8bce643-09b0-5d80-8424-21d9d82141fb","html":"<p>After a couple of years using Medium as my blog, I decided to move away from Medium and\nuse <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Gatsby</a> (a static website generator).</p>\n<h4 id=\"main-issues-with-medium-were\"><a href=\"#main-issues-with-medium-were\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Main issues with Medium were:</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Limited articles readers can access.</li>\n<li>No code highlight for code-snippets (I always thought this was something that Medium would fix with the time),\nthe only alternative was using <a href=\"https://gist.github.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Github Gists</a> but this means that I need to create a Gist\nfor every code-snippet that I wanted to show. </li>\n<li>Internet access was require to write a build my articles.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>After checking some alternatives, I ended up considering Gatsby as a really good alternative for the job.</p>\n<h4 id=\"main-advantages-of-using-gatsby\"><a href=\"#main-advantages-of-using-gatsby\" aria-hidden class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Main advantages of using Gatsby:</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Free hosting using multiples hosting solutions: Github Pages (I’m using this), Netlify and more…</li>\n<li>Static generated (no need for a server to render the pages) during build time.</li>\n<li>I can compose and write articles without internet connection using markdown and view the final\nresult in my local environment</li>\n<li>Advance code highlight - I’m using syntax theme based on <a href=\"https://github.com/sdras/night-owl-vscode-theme/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://github.com/sdras/night-owl-vscode-theme/</a> </li>\n</ul>\n<p>Example: </p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight has-highlighted-lines\" data-language=\"php\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber 0\" class=\"language-php line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-php\"><span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\"><span class=\"token keyword\">class</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">DynamoDbMessageRepository</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">implements</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">MessageRepository</span></span><span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span></span>    <span class=\"token comment\">/**\n     * @var DynamoDbClient\n     */</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">protected</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$client</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\">/**\n     * @var MessageSerializer\n     */</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">protected</span> MessageSerializer <span class=\"token variable\">$serializer</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\">/**\n     * @var string\n     */</span>\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">protected</span> string <span class=\"token variable\">$tableName</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">__construct</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>DynamoDbClient <span class=\"token variable\">$client</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> MessageSerializer <span class=\"token variable\">$serializer</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> string <span class=\"token variable\">$tableName</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"token variable\">$this</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token property\">client</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$client</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n        <span class=\"token variable\">$this</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token property\">serializer</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$serializer</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"gatsby-highlight-code-line\">        <span class=\"token variable\">$this</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token property\">tableName</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$tableName</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></span>    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token keyword\">public</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">function</span> <span class=\"token function\">retrieveAll</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>AggregateRootId <span class=\"token variable\">$id</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> Generator\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n        <span class=\"token variable\">$query</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n            <span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'TableName'</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token variable\">$this</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token property\">tableName</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n            <span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'KeyConditionExpression'</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'aggregateRootId = :v1'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n            <span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'ExpressionAttributeValues'</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span>\n                <span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">':v1'</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">[</span><span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'S'</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span> <span class=\"token variable\">$id</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token function\">toString</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n            <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span>\n        <span class=\"token punctuation\">]</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n        <span class=\"token variable\">$result</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$this</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token property\">client</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token function\">getPaginator</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token single-quoted-string string\">'Query'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$query</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n        <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token variable\">$this</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token function\">yieldMessagesForResult</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token variable\">$result</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span></code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\n<ul>\n<li>Great documentation and integration. Gatsby integrates almost with anything and more important it expose\nto developers always the same API in GraphQL independent of what you are connecting\nto (MySQL, Headless CMS, Wordpress, etc…).</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Until now, it has been a great experience and I highly recommend you to give it a try. </p>\n<hr>","timeToRead":2,"frontmatter":{"title":"Moving away from Medium","date":"June 16, 2020","spoiler":"After a couple of years using Medium as my blog, I decided to move away from Medium and use Gatsby (a static website generator)."},"fields":{"slug":"/moving-from-medium-to-static-blog/","langKey":"en","tags":["blog","gatsby","github"]}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/moving-from-medium-to-static-blog/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/automating-uniplaces-git-flow/","langKey":"en","directoryName":"automating-uniplaces-git-flow","maybeAbsoluteLinks":[]},"frontmatter":{"title":"3 years at Uniplaces… and still counting!"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/blue-green-deployments-with-aws-lambda/","langKey":"en","directoryName":"blue-green-deployments-with-aws-lambda","maybeAbsoluteLinks":[]},"frontmatter":{"title":"Blue/Green deployments with AWS Lambda"}},"translations":[],"translatedLinks":[]}}}